<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Statute" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Statute,</orth> 1) an edict, a law: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.322.67" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 322</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.126.6" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 85</bibl> (F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>statues</emph>). <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.213" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.7.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 7, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 76</bibl>.<lb />2) a bond; a mortgage: <cit><quote>the s. of thy beauty thou wilt take, thou usurer, that put' st forth all to use,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 134.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 134, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a great buyer of land, with his --s, his recognizances,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 113</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>